 than a mount."],[122,"Example"],[99,"Expect 3-5 days on a Pi 5 with a fast SSD. The bottleneck is not\ndownload speed. Bitcoin Core verifies every digital signature in\nevery transaction ever recorded, and that takes time. A slower\nmachine or a spinning hard drive can push past a week."],[678,"Expected output (version number will drift):"],[815,"Expected output (your number will differ):"],[223,"Expected output (your subnet will differ):"],[1069,"Expected output, a `v22.x` line from `node`, and a `10.x` or\nnewer line from `npm`:"],[338,"Expected output, a `v22.x` line from `node`, and a `10.x` or newer\nline from `npm`:"],[279,"Expected output:"],[473,"Expected output:"],[477,"Expected output:"],[685,"Expected output:"],[774,"Expected output:"],[782,"Expected output:"],[937,"Expected output:"],[945,"Expected output:"],[1061,"Expose RTL through Caddy"],[102,"Ext4 isn't compatible with Windows out of the box. Tools like\nLinux File Systems for Windows\n(Paragon, 10-day free trial) let you mount the drive read/write. On\nmacOS, extFS for Mac\ndoes the same."],[528,"Extra explorers, wallets, alternative Electrum servers, privacy tools, and testnet setup."],[1134,"Extra Lightning tooling, dashboards, liquidity managers, fee automation, alternative implementations, and wallets."],[944,"Extract the archive and install both binaries:"],[82,"FAQ"],[1288,"Fast and nimble Electrum-compatible SPV server, a performance-focused alternative to Electrs."],[1310,"Fast Electrum-compatible SPV server, alternative to Electrs."],[1284,"Feature-rich desktop Bitcoin wallet for power users, connected to your own Electrum server."],[1305,"Feature-rich desktop wallet for power users."],[673,"Fetch the Tor Project's signing key, dearmor it into a keyring\nfile, and clean up the original:"],[1107,"Fetch, find the latest tag, check it out, verify the signature,\nreinstall dependencies:"],[215,"Find the entry for your enclosure. The interesting bit is the\n`idVendor:idProduct` pair, something